Second Department,

October, 1954.

(October 4, 1954.) Edwin F. Borgos et al., Appellants, v. Edward G. Duerstein et al., Respondents.

Respondents’ motion for leave to appeal to the Court of Appeals denied. Application by the County Clerk of Westchester County for leave to become a party to this proceeding and to prosecute an appeal to the Court of Appeals denied, without costs. Present — Adel, Acting P. J., Wenzel, MacCrate, Schmidt and Beldock, JJ. [See 283 App. Div. 1069.]
